headline.main: Nearly 1,300 Rescued Migrants Arrive in Sicily Over Weekend
headline.print_headline: Nearly 1,300 Rescued Migrants Arrive in Sicily Over Weekend

lead_paragraph: Almost 1,300 migrants arrived in Sicily on rescue ships over the weekend after crossing the Mediterranean, while a 16-year-old boy died on one of the ships, Italy's Coast Guard said.
